Support pickle with kurt objects.

Added testing to verify simple projects can be pickled.

Note: At this time only pickle.HIGHEST_PROTOCOL is supported. To support older
protocols, all classes that define __getattr__ or __slots__ need to be updated
to include __getdata__ and __setdata__. This requires changes or monkeypatches
to construct.

Fix and verify that pickle files can be loaded.

Remove parser state tracking

Because it's not actually helpful for debugging

Watcher.__init__(): doc: block to watch variable

To construct a watcher for a variable, the block should be
'readVariable' not 'getVar:' (which is not recognised as a block).

(The final project file does need to specify 'getVar:'; the conversion
is done in

    scratch20.ZipWriter.save_watcher()
    scratch14.Serializer.save_watcher()

on the way out and

    scratch20.ZipReader.load_watcher()
    scratch14.Serializer.load_watcher()

on the way in.)
